Usage: copy_bump [-help] [-assigned] [-name_format {format}] -shift {X Y} {-bumps {bump_list} | -selected }

-help                  # Prints out the command usage
-assigned              # Copy the bumps with assigned signals (bool, optional)
-bumps {bump_list}     # Specifies names of bumps to be copied
                       # (string, optional)
-name_format {format}  # Specifies the name format for the target bumps
                       # (string, optional)
-selected              # Copy the selected bumps (bool, optional)
-shift {X Y}           # Specifies the distance in microns from the source
                       # location to the target location in X/Y direction
                       # (string, required)